rComments: If you don't plan on attending the classes know that the power points aren't enough to cover the lesson, but he gave a weekly quiz so you have to stay updated. A lot of reading to do but he's a great teacher and it's not hard to pass with an A, he did his best keeping the class entertaining and proposed creative ways to teach ! Would take it again.
teacherRatingTags: ['Clear grading criteria', 'Get ready to read', 'Gives good feedback']

rComments: Exercices d'écriture à propos des textes philosophique chaque semaine, qui aide pour les trois dissertations. Allez le voir si vous avez des questions, surtout pour les projets. Il est d'une grande aide et très gentil. Il a à cœur la réussite de ses élèves. Vraiment drôle et passionné. Il rend la philosophie plus agréable. Travailler porte fruit.

One of the best professors I've ever had. His lectures are extremely well done (thorough and uses funny examples so students understand), and though he does require a one paged assignment once a week, I find it to be a perfect way to improve research skills and learn about what themes/philosophers we'll be seeing next in class. He's very caring!
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', 'Accessible outside class', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Though he is passionate by what he teaches, his classes aren't interesting at all. He'll give you a paper (1-2 pages) to do every week that seems like a lot but that prepares you for the evaluations. Go see him before handing in your papers because he'll give you a ton of hints. Be sure to be very specific and clear in your assignments.

He's very passionate about what he teaches, which makes lectures fly by but sometimes very heavy on the brain. He provides VERY clear grading criteria for his evaluations and he is easily accesible outside of class. All in all, he's a good Prof and I would certainly recommend him for philosophie moderne.

Fantastic prof, loves to teach. Very open and willing to help. He's very dynamic. If he ever asks you if the world is round, just say that you don't know for sure if it is. Final exam was very long, but they tend to be open book.
Excellent professeur: compétent, clair, disponible. La structure des évaluations permet d'atteindre une compréhension en profondeur de la matière. Il en faudrait plus comme lui!

Un des professeurs les plus intéressant et les plus organisés de mon Bac. Il est vraiment bon pour ses étudiants et te donne tous les outils pour réussir son cours mais ses cours demandent beaucoup de temps (travaux) et beaucoup de lectures
really good teacher.

Prof très dynamique qui adore la participation des étudiants dans ses cours. Il rend le cours endurable et facile pour ceux qui doivent prendre ce cours obligatoirement puis enrichissant pour ceux qui se spécialisent dans le domaine. L'examen mi-session est à livre ouvert puis l'examen final est un projet.
Very good prof! He knows what he's talking about. I loved the fact that there was a final project instead of an exam! My best teacher for 1st year!

I found him boring! I would not recommend taking his classes! It is my first philosophy class and now I HATE IT!! He founds himself funny and it gets long and annoying! He is deffinitly passionate about what he teaches but I did not appreciate the class at all!
Class is complicated. Although, he doesn't give a final exam, but a final project.
Awesome class !
Interesting, good and helpful

Really good prof. Makes sure students understand completely. Available outside class time for questions. Makes difficult philosophers very easy to comprehend. Cares about whether students like the class. Friendly and kinda funny. Very French, but very good at English, and always translates French ideas for English-speaking students.

Il est un bon prof, j'étais surpris quand j'ai vu qu'il était tellement jeune. Moi personnellement, j'ai eu de la misère car la philo n'est pas ma niche, mais une très bon prof quand même. Il essait tellement d'être drôle, il a un sens d'humour, mais parfois pas tellement drôle.

Excellent prof. Very passionate about what he teaches. He managed to make philosophy somewhat tolerable for me. Jokes are somewhat lame but funny because he tries and finds them hilarious. Very nice person when you visit him during office hours.
Il connait ce qu'il enseigne, et explique très bien ce qu'il s'attend de ses étudiants pour les travaux.  Il fait des petite blagues plâte des fois.  En général c'est un bon prof.
Great prof. Knows his sheeeet. Unclear and frustrating midterm BUT gives you great chances at improving your mark with bonus exercises through the rest of the term. Très interessant.
